    "recap_headline": "University of North Florida",
    "recap_text": "DELAND, FLA. -\nNorth Florida Baseball evened its road series at Stetson with a dominant run-rule win, 12-1, at Conrad Park on Saturday.\nNorth Florida's offense got off to a hot start in the top of the first inning. Redshirt junior utility player\nJackson Toberman\nplated junior infielder\nMitchell Collins\nwith a sacrifice fly for UNF's first run of the game. Redshirt junior utility player\nBoone Hosey\ndrove an RBI single up the middle to extend North Florida's lead to 2-0.\nStetson responded with its only run in the bottom of the first frame.\nNorth Florida broke the game open in the top of the second with three home runs and six runs in the inning. Redshirt sophomore outfielder\nCarter White\ngot the scoring started with a three-run home run, allowing North Florida to command a 5-1 advantage.\nJunior infielder\nMathew Farner\nand Toberman delivered back-to-back home runs later in the second inning to put the Ospreys ahead 8-1. It marked Toberman's second home run of the season and Farner's seventh.\nWhite belted his second home run of the game in the top of the third inning. His second homer gave North Florida a 10-1 advantage. White notched his third home run and seventh RBI of the game in the top of the seventh frame to help secure the run-rule win. He now has five home runs this season.\nSophomore right-handed pitcher\nTrevor Nikolis\ndealt seven innings and allowed just four hits and one earned run while posting six strikeouts en route to the win.\nNORTH FLORIDA\u00a012, STETSON 1\nPitchers of Record\nWin:\nTrevor Nikolis\n(1-1)\nLoss:\nEthan Phillips (1-3)\nLine Scores\nUNF\n| 12 R, 14 H, 0 E\nSTET\n| 1 R, 4 H, 1 E\nStatistical Leaders\nNORTH FLORIDA\nCarter White\n| 3-4, 7 RBI, 3 HR, 3 R\nMathew Farner\n| 2-4, 1 HR, 2 RBI, 2 R, 1 BB\nJackson Toberman\n| 1-3, 2 RBI, 1 HR, 1 R,\nMitchell Collins\n| 3-5, 2 R\nTrevor Nikolis\n| 7.0 IP, 4 H, 1 R, 1 ER, 6 K, 2 BB\nSTETSON\nFoster Apple | 0-1, 1 RBI, 1 BB\nUP NEXT\nNorth Florida remains at Conrad Park for a rubber match at Stetson on Sunday, March 15 at noon ET."
